[Student "S"]
{NORTH has 13 points and four cards in both \Hs and \Ss. Rather 
than bid one of them she makes a Negative Double, promising four cards in EACH of them. It's like 
she was able to bid 1\H\S.

SOUTH doesn't have four cards in either Major, but with a \D stopper he bids 1NT.

NORTH happily bids 3NT.}

